# --- Canonical .claude/ ignore block. Paste into each repo's .gitignore. ---
# Ignore contents by default, but auto-track durable, reusable assets.
# Use `.claude/*` (NOT `.claude/`) so git descends and the `!` re-includes work —
# git will not descend into a fully-ignored directory, so `!.claude/x/` under a
# bare `.claude/` silently does nothing.
.claude/*
!.claude/agents/
!.claude/hooks/
!.claude/skills/
!.claude/workflows/
# .claude/worktrees/ is intentionally left ignored (agent worktrees, not assets).
